<br>
     There are two types of proficiencies in Anarchy’s system; abilities and skills.  Abilities are strength, agility, stamina, intelligence, sense and psychic.  Skills are everything else, including body development and nano pool.  The starting value and aptitude of abilities varies with race.  The starting value and aptitude of skills varies with class.<br>
<br>
     I have come up with two basic formulas for mapping out the progress of your character.  With these formulas it is possible to know what ability or skill level you will have at level 200; based upon how many improvement points you spend in any given skill.  Abilities and skills can be calculated exactly; also with the increase of abilities skills increase at a ratio of 1:4; this is covered further in the skills section of this document.  This is good news because everyone will reach their goal at a much reduced improvement point cost.  I’m not sure how many improvement points are given up to level 200, but I do have a theory based on player input.<br>
<br>
(1,500 x 1) + (4,000 x 13) + (10,000 x 35) + (20,000 x 50) + (40,000 x 50) +  (80,000 x 40) + (160,000 x 11) = 8,363,500 improvement points<br>
<br>
Abilities<br>
<br>
     Abilities increase in multiples, example; a solitus increase in strength has a multiple of 2 and  from level  5 to 6 costs 10 ip, from 6 to 7 costs 12 ip; in effect 10, 12, 14, 16 and so on.  There are three multipliers; 1, 2 and 3.  The free cost of your ability starting values must be subtracted from the end result since you don’t pay for those initial levels.<br>
<br>
[(1+N) x (N/2) x M] - F <br>
<br>
N represents the level goal you would like to reach, M represents the standard multiplier and F represents the free improvements points required to reach your starting value.  Those values are as follows.<br>
<br>
STRENGTH:<br>
(atrox M = 2 / F = 210)     (nano M = 3 / F = 9)     (opifex M = 2 / F = 6)     (solitus M = 2 / F = 30)<br>
AGILITY:<br>
(atrox M = 2 / F = 30)     (nano M = 3 / F = 9)     (opifex M = 1 / F = 105)     (solitus M = 2 / F = 30)<br>
STAMINA:<br>
(atrox M = 1 / F = 54)     (nano M = 2 / F = 6)     (opifex M = 3 / F = 45)     (solitus M = 2 / F = 30)<br>
INTELLIGENCE:<br>
(atrox M = 3 / F = 9)     (nano M = 1 / F = 105)     (opifex M = 2 / F = 30)     (solitus M = 2 / F = 30)<br>
SENSE:<br>
(atrox M = 3 / F = 9)     (nano M = 2 / F = 30)     (opifex M = 1 / F = 45)     (solitus M = 2 / F = 30)<br>
PSYCHIC:<br>
(atrox M = 3 / F = 9)     (nano M = 1 / F = 45)     (opifex M = 2 / F = 6)     (solitus M = 2 / F = 30)<br>
<br>
     The formula (1+N) x (N/2) is a means of adding 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 etc and unfortunately in the context of Anarchy’s I.P. system only works if you subtract 1 from the value of N; except for abilities that have a multiplier of 1; in those cases the 1 is subtracted after the math is calculated. so if your goal is level 900 you must use 899 for the value of N.  You can use 900 but you’d be paying for an extra skill level.  This is because level 1is never paid for since 0 can’t be multiplied.  Examples:  <br>
<br>
Atrox   character wanting 300 stamina [(300+1) x (300/2) -1] -54 = 45,095 improvement points <br>
Solitus character wanting 300 stamina [(299+1) x (299/2) x2] -30 = 89,670 improvement points<br>
Opifex character wanting 300 stamina [(299+1) x (299/2) x3] -45 = 134,505 improvements points<br>
     <br>
Skills<br>
<br>
     Skills differ from abilities since they have no multiplier.  Instead they have an inflation value of 20% per level.  For example; a character’s most proficient skill costs 5 improvements points per level plus a 20% increase per level, so at this rate the character would add an additional 1 point per level; thus you would get 5 + 6 + 7 + 8 + 9 etc.  The base cost is always directly proportional to the inflation cost, so a base of 5 has an inflation of 1, 5.5 has an inflation of 1.1, 6 has 1.2, 6.5 has 1.3 and so on.  Multiply your inflation by 5 or divide your base by 5 if you only have one value and aren’t sure what the other is.<br>
<br>
B + (BxN) + [(1+N) x (N/2) xI]<br>
<br>
     B represents the base cost , N represents the level goal you would like to reach, I represents the inflation value.  Again because of the nature of  the formula and Anarchy’s free skill levels at start up, you must subtract your starting value and 1 from the variable N before calculating.  The starting value will be 5, 6 or 7.  The extra 1 is because the first increase in skill has no inflation cost.  So starting value plus one would be 6, 7 or 8 to subtract from variable N.  Here are some examples:<br>
<br>
M. Artist wants 800 body dev. 7.5 + (7.5x793) + [(1+793) x (793/2) x1.5] = 478,187 improvement points<br>
M. Artist wants 800 com literacy 10 + (10x793) + [(1+793) x (793/2) x2] = 635,996 improvement points<br>
M. Artist wants 400 matt crea. 12 + (12x393) + [(1+393) x (393/2) x2.4] = 190,538 improvement points<br>
<br>
     With the increase of abilities; skills increase at a steady rate of 1:4.  The formula for calculating this free bonus is as follows.  The total should be subtracted from the N variable in the basic skills formula above.  Take the ability level you have or plan to achieve and multiply that value by 25%, then multiply the result by the % of dependence of the relevant skill.<br>
<br>
Y x .25 x P<br>
<br>
     Y represents the value of the given ability and P represents the ability’s % of dependence to the relative skill.  Examples follow.<br>
<br>
Character has a 300 intelligence.  The computer literacy bonus is 300 x .25 x 1.0 = 75<br>
Character has a 300 intelligence.  The psychology bonus is 300 x .25 x .5 = 37.5 (38 round up)<br>
Character has a 400 strength.  The shotgun bonus is 400 x .25 x .4 = 40<br>
